  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_414",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_414"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_132"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "My home country, Finland, shares the EUâs longest border with Russiaâover 1,300 kilometres.\nThe Finnish Defence Forces have shown how decades of commitment is now bearing fruit.\nConscription, military training, and investments in defence have long been among the EUâs best.\nWe are ready to defend our borders.\nMeanwhile, some EU countries have neglected their duties, keeping defence spending minimal while expecting others to bear the burden.\nNow the era of free riding is over â we cannot start to fund countries that have failed to prepare.\nDefence is not a charity - itâs everyoneâs duty."
      },
      {
        "@value": "Given the absence of the Council in the debate, I will give the floor directly to Commissioner Jørgensen."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T20:25:35"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_481",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_481"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_22"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_54"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Ten tweede is er een ander probleem van het industriebeleid. Dat is dat we de laatste jaren heel veel publiek geld, belastinggeld, hebben gegeven aan bedrijven die dat in hun eigen zakken hebben gestoken, aan de aandeelhouders hebben gegeven zonder banen te garanderen in Europa. Ook op dat vlak schiet de Commissie tekort. Welke garanties zijn er voor de arbeiders, voor de werknemers?\nTen derde wilt u nu ook nog eens de sociale en ecologische verantwoordelijkheid van multinationals afzwakken wat betreft ruwe grondstoffen. Dat wil zeggen dat we meer plunderingen zullen zien in Oost-Congo, dat we Rwanda nog meer zullen aanmoedigen om daar de oorlog op te stoken. Dat is niet de oplossing. Wij hebben een publiek industriebeleid nodig."
      },
      {
        "@value": "Le colpe che non non vengono perdonate al popolo armeno sono di due nature: la prima è geografica: interrompere la continuità territoriale tra Azerbaigian e Turchia; e la seconda, è culturale: il popolo armeno è un popolo cristiano.\nLe domande che il popolo armeno rivolge all'Europa sono domande degne di un popolo europeo. Diciamolo chiaramente! Questo significa, che a noi europei, è chiesto di valutare se siamo disposti a riservare agli azeri lo stesso trattamento che riserviamo ai russi per come non rispettano la libertà dell'Ucraina.\nSanzioni vere e la libertà per questi 23 cittadini illegalmente detenuti."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T21:28:16"
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T22:03:32"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_547",
