      },
      {
        "@value": "SoustÅeÄme se na posilovÃ¡nÃ­ aliance NATO. Investujme diplomatickÃ© ÃºsilÃ­ i finanÄnÃ­ zdroje do tohoto projektu. Je potÅeba se zastavit a o obrannÃ© politice pÅemÃ½Å¡let s chladnou hlavou. NaÅ¡e vzÃ¡jemnÃ© vztahy se SpojenÃ½mi stÃ¡ty americkÃ½mi nynÃ­ omezujeme pouze na otÃ¡zku Ukrajiny a nechÃ¡vÃ¡me je definovat tÃ­mto konfliktem. PÅitom je zde mnoho jinÃ½ch problÃ©mÅ¯, na kterÃ½ch potÅebujeme spolupracovat. MÄli bychom vyvinout maximÃ¡lnÃ­ ÃºsilÃ­ na zajiÅ¡tÄnÃ­ mÃ­ru a vytvoÅenÃ­ fungujÃ­cÃ­ch bezpeÄnostnÃ­ch zÃ¡ruk. ChytrÃ© a zodpovÄdnÃ© ÅeÅ¡enÃ­ je zajiÅ¡tÄnÃ­ konkurenceschopnosti naÅ¡eho hospodÃ¡ÅstvÃ­, udrÅ¾ovÃ¡nÃ­ pro Evropu vÃ½hodnÃ½ch transatlantickÃ½ch vztahÅ¯ a vedenÃ­ pragmatickÃ© diplomatickÃ© politiky."
      },
      {
        "@value": "In the Commission's plan, there is one page about workers. They want to give them a little bit of unemployment benefits, then give them random jobs and waste their skills.\nLike Audi Brussels, for example: highly qualified workers trained to produce electric cars, now all fired. Instead of making electric cars, now they want to build weapons and move the production to Mexico. Absurd.\nIt is the same with Van Hool, an ultra-modern bus company going bankrupt because the Flemish Government decided to buy buses outside of the EU.\nAnd the EU wakes up now, but this crisis started a long time ago, and they want again to give billions of your taxpayers' money to the same companies that created this crisis. As a former car worker, I refuse to be silent while my colleagues are getting fired by the thousands.\nWe can make electric cars here for modern, clean mobility. We have the capacity, we have the skills, so let's do it."
      }
    ],
