    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_40"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_24"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Esta proposta de regulamento Ã© o projeto racista da extremaâdireita que dÃ¡ aos governos da extremaâdireita a cobertura legal que atÃ© agora nÃ£o tinham.\nÃ uma polÃ­tica que faz da expulsÃ£o dos migrantes a regra, que torna sistemÃ¡tica a detenÃ§Ã£o em massa de pessoas sem documentos, que admite a deportaÃ§Ã£o forÃ§ada de migrantes para paÃ­ses terceiros onde nunca estiveram e com que nunca tiveram contacto. Uma polÃ­tica que admite a detenÃ§Ã£o e a expulsÃ£o de menores, incluindo de menores nÃ£o acompanhados, apenas os salvando de serem enviados para esses paÃ­ses terceiros que lhes sÃ£o desconhecidos. Esta Ã© uma polÃ­tica que levarÃ¡ as pessoas migrantes a continuarem a ser exploradas, escondidas de quem os persegue e de quem os quer deter.\nHÃ¡ alternativas que a ComissÃ£o nÃ£o quis considerar, e, por isso, contarÃ¡ com a nossa oposiÃ§Ã£o.\n(O orador aceita responder a uma pergunta Â«cartÃ£o azulÂ»)"
      },
      {
        "@value": "Ich stimme Frau Kommissarin zu, die gesagt hat: Wenn die Stimme der Beschäftigten gehört wird, stärkt das die Resilienz in den Unternehmen. Und wir wissen aus so vielen Studien: Da, wo wir mitbestimmte Unternehmen haben, die sind nachhaltiger, die sind innovativer, die sind krisenfester und am Ende auch wirtschaftlich erfolgreicher – und deshalb ist es ein Wettbewerbsvorteil.\nUnd wenn jetzt die Arbeitgeber Mails rumschicken und alle Abgeordneten auffordern, gegen den Bericht zu stimmen, weil sie sagen, das schadet der Wettbewerbsfähigkeit, beeinträchtigt die Geschwindigkeit von Entscheidungen, kann ich nur sagen: Hören Sie nicht auf diese Argumente aus der Mottenkiste – das schadet uns, unserer Wirtschaft und auch dem europäischen Sozialmodell."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T16:22:54"
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T16:52:48"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/creitem32",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Topic"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "creitem32"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#name": [
      {
        "@value": "The need for EU support towards a just transition and reconstruction in Syria (RC-B10-0157/2025)"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_519",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_519"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_349"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Only a few words on the latest outbreak of violence. So we welcome, as I already said, the announcement by the interim authorities to support the investigative commission which is being established. Everything must be done to prevent any such crimes from happening again. This is why I said at the beginning that they had to translate their commitment into action.\nOn the Brussels conference, once again we think that it is a very important one, and a little bit different than earlier. For the first time, the Syrian interim authorities have been invited together with the United Nations, alongside Syria's neighbouring countries and other regional partners. There will be two different panels and two different pledges. One will be to address the immediate needs of the Syrian people, with the focus on socioâeconomic recovery. At the same time, it will be addressing the serious humanitarian needs which still exist.\nOn the different groups, some of you mentioned the Christians and the protection of Christian minorities or communities. You all know that the new authorities in Damascus have a major responsibility to ensure the protection of all components of society and to refrain from acts of vengeance. We are sure that this their task, but let's see what the future will bring. Of course, we have to protect all Syrians in their diversity, based on the equal rights of citizens.Â Once again, a very important issue is to support the inclusive transition in Syria, because it is critical for the regional security.\nOn returns â returns cannot and should not be rushed. In the context of a very fragile transition, something which we want to see is whether and at what moment Syria will be proclaimed a safe third country. So let's see how this will go.\nOn sanctions, we have already suspended sectoral sanctions, but now let's see how to proceed with financial sanctions. We know that American sanctions are already there. So let's see.\nAll that we have been doing in January and February at the Foreign Affairs Council has been in a gradual and irreversible manner. I want to thank you for the support you have shown this evening. Syria's reconstruction will need the backing of all of us â of the Commission, of the Member States and of Parliament â in a Team Europe spirit. Parliamentary diplomacy, outreach and expertise in stateâbuilding are of the essence at this critical juncture for Syria. What is important is that we here in Europe remain united and committed, and Syria's future depends on our collective action today. So we are looking forward to the resolution, which I hope will be voted tomorrow."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T22:26:10"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_436",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_436"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_312"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_84"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Brussel beweert dat deze deal de Europese industrie moet versterken. Maar tegelijk worden bedrijven verplicht tot peperdure CO2-reducties, extra regelgeving en torenhoge energiekosten. De oplossing is niet nog een Europees plan, maar het afschaffen van de Green Deal. We moeten daarom inzetten op drie zaken: ten eerste betaalbare energie door kernenergie, ten tweede bescherming van onze industrie tegen oneerlijke concurrentie, en ten derde minder EU-bemoeienis en minder bureaucratie. Want enkel op die manier heeft de industrie weer toekomst in Europa."
      },
      {
        "@value": "Und dementsprechend möchte ich diesen EU Consumers Day nutzen, um Ihnen diese Geschichte mitzugeben. Bitte denken Sie immer daran, dass das Verbraucherschutzrecht der Europäischen Union einer der Bereiche ist, in dem unsere Bürgerinnen und Bürger am allermeisten berührt werden."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T20:31:01"
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T21:01:17"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_537",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_537"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_374"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "The fact is that after Israel once again cut off electricity to Gaza, nine out of ten people no longer have access to safe drinking water. Nine out of ten.\nThe fact is that after Israel once again halted the delivery of humanitarian aid to Gaza, the genocide is only escalating. Generations are being wiped out before our eyes. And still the powerful are turning a blind one or worse.\nIf those of you who had even a shred â just a shred â of humanity in you, you would not look away. You would not excuse the inexcusable. You would do something that should have been done long ago. You would deliver."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T22:57:42"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_89",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#hasRole": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/role_participant_89"
      }
