  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_319",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_319"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_233"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_1"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "After numerous wake-up calls we have discussed here, Europe's moment of truth has finally arrived. We're not starting from scratch. In MarchÂ 2022, the 27Â heads of state or government adopted the Strategic Compass. A year later, the Commission published the European Defence Industrial Strategy, and we also adopted ASAP and EDIRPA and agreed on the capability development priorities.\nAll these initiatives are slowly but surely pushing Member States to step outside their national corridors in pursuit of a genuine European Defence Union. But now we really have to make a great leap.\nTherefore, dear Commissioner Kubilius, the white paper must build on these achievements, and propose regulatory and programmatic initiatives at European level, rather than confining itself to a description of threats and shared needs.\nYou, dear Commissioner, and the HR/VP have a chance to significantly steer this debate. I look forward to discussing the white paper thoroughly at committee level."
      },
      {
        "@value": ""
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
