    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_384"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "What were Israel's options? Do nothing? Accept any demand made by the terrorists while the hostages were still being held? No country in the world would tolerate this! The EU did not negotiate with ISIS, nor did the US negotiate with Al-Qaeda!\nJust as the EU sees peace negotiations between Russia and Ukraine as dangerous and invalid without security guarantees for Ukraine, it should analyse the situation between Israel and Gaza in the same manner, as long as the hostages are not released. If not, let us admit that we are applying double standards in EU institutions.\nIf we truly want peace, we should start by standing with those fighting against terrorism, not by legitimizing those who practice it - including here, in Europe, in Brussels, Strasbourg, Paris, and many other places.\nWhich of our children will be the terroristsâ next victim?"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_369",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Participant"
