    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Az infrastrukturÃ¡lis fejlesztÃ©sek hiÃ¡nya mÃ¡shol is Ã©rezteti a hatÃ¡sÃ¡t. PÃ©ldÃ¡ul 2029 elÅtt nem vÃ¡rhatÃ³ak Ãºj szÃ©lerÅmÅ±- kapacitÃ¡sok, a hÃ¡lÃ³zati csatlakozÃ¡sok szÅ±kÃ¶ssÃ©ge miatt. A magyar ipar kiszolgÃ¡ltatottsÃ¡gÃ¡t tovÃ¡bbÃ¡ nÃ¶veli az is, hogy bÃ¡r a kormÃ¡ny elhanyagolta az energiaberuhÃ¡zÃ¡sokat, most adÃ³fizetÅi pÃ©nzbÅl csÃ¡bÃ­tja be a gigÃ¡szi energiaÃ©hsÃ©gÅ± kÃ­nai akkumulÃ¡torgyÃ¡rakat Ã©s autÃ³gyÃ¡rakat. Ãgy pedig tovÃ¡bb emelkednek az Ã¡ramÃ¡rak, amelyek kÃ¶zvetlenÃ¼l a magyar vÃ¡llalkozÃ¡sok versenykÃ©pessÃ©gÃ©t is veszÃ©lyeztetik.\nA magyar helyzet megmutatja, milyen kÃ¡rokat tud okozni a megfizethetÅ energiakÃ­nÃ¡lat hiÃ¡nya a versenykÃ©pessÃ©gnek. Ezzel szemben a tiszta ipari megÃ¡llapodÃ¡sban kijelÃ¶lt stratÃ©gia kivÃ¡lÃ³ alapot ad a fenntarthatÃ³ eurÃ³pai iparfejlesztÃ©snek."
      },
      {
        "@value": "This is the reason why many Uyghurs escape the brutal regime while placing their trust in the hands of the international community. Thailand has completely failed these victims and violated international guarantees of their dignity and rights. They were kept in inhumane conditions before being sent back to China, where they face the risk of torture and imprisonment.\nDear colleagues, this is yet another proof of why we have to rethink our relations with China, ensuring a value-based and consistent approach towards the Chinese Communist Party. Only such a principled foreign policy can protect human rights and our economic interests. Thailand and our partner countries have to decide where they want to stand."
      }
    ],
