      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T21:16:51"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_326",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_326"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_81"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_238"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": ""
      },
      {
        "@value": "The state assets of Russia located abroad must be used directly for the needs of Ukraine to restore its urban and civil infrastructure, environment and property lost by the people. The use of interest from frozen Russian assets is good, but it's not enough to compensate for the losses suffered by Ukraine. Russian assets must be frozen and used either to directly compensate for the needs of Ukraine and reconstruction, or to become a guarantee when issuing state bonds or taking out the necessary loans.\nI call upon the Member States to find and agree on a comprehensive legal approach."
      }
    ],
