    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Member States say they do as well, but I'm not sure, at least not about all of them â your Member State excluded. They have had their chance to get European defence right, but they squandered precious time and opportunity for the last 15 years. Despite programmes, funds, platforms to promote true European cooperation, Member States have proven unable to rise above narrow national interests. And this costs us military ability, precious money and desirable jobs.\nEuropean security is a collective public good for all citizens. It should go hand in hand with resilient societies, with sound education, care and social fabric. No contradiction there. We need a truly European approach to defence that includes European financing, European planning, development, procurement and operational command. Let's get to work."
      },
      {
        "@value": ""
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T19:26:05"
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T19:52:36"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_79",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_79"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_53"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_68"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_65"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Finally, the EU has woken up to the fact that the complex and duplicated regulatory requirements are weighing on European businesses. I urge my colleagues in this House and all Member States to act swiftly on these proposals, to keep their eyes on the objective and not try to reopen and rehash political debates that were settled when these pieces of legislation were adopted.\nI call on the Commission to keep up the momentum and continue to simplification agenda without diluting our ambition or its intent. We must assess the framework for each of our industries and ensure they're not being unnecessarily burdened.\nHowever, acting swiftly does not mean acting recklessly. This Parliament needs to carefully scrutinise the Omnibus proposals to ensure that they are truly bringing forward simplification measures and not deregulation for the sake of it.\nI think there is a big debate that is required in this particular House with regard to deregulation and simplification, and I do not think that we should be using deregulation to throw out the ambition that this Parliament, the Commission and the Council set in the last mandate."
      },
      {
        "@value": "Les grandes tempÃªtes exigent de rompre avec lâhabitude, et le moment est venu pour nous aussi de nous dÃ©faire de nos meubles. La Russie nous menace directement, et les Ãtats-Unis nous abandonnent lÃ¢chement. Eh bien, câest le moment de vÃ©ritÃ© de lâEurope.\nIl nous revient dÃ©sormais, Ã  nous et Ã  nous seuls, dâaider massivement notre premiÃ¨re ligne de dÃ©fense quâest la rÃ©sistance ukrainienne. Le Conseil europÃ©en lâaffirme, mais cela suppose de prendre des dÃ©cisions fortes, devant lesquelles nos Ãtats reculent encore, comme la saisie des 209Â milliards dâavoirs publics russes gelÃ©s en Europe et leur affectation Ã  lâUkraine.\nIl nous revient aussi dÃ©sormais, Ã  nous et Ã  nous seuls, dâassurer notre propre sÃ©curitÃ© et de construire une dÃ©fense autonome. Nos dirigeants lâaffirment, mais cela suppose dâaller plus loin que ce qui fut annoncÃ© jeudi. LanÃ§ons un emprunt commun finanÃ§ant des programmes europÃ©ens et assurons-nous que cet argent serve Ã  dÃ©velopper les industries europÃ©ennes âÂ et pas Ã  empiler les F-35.\nNous avons besoin dâagir plus, et plus en EuropÃ©ens. Ð¡Ð»Ð°Ð²Ð° Ð£ÐºÑÐ°ÑÐ½Ñ (Â«Slava OukraÃ¯niÂ»)! Vive lâEurope libre!"
      },
      {
        "@value": "Mientras China y los Estados Unidos protegen y subsidian a sus fabricantes, Europa impone regulaciones que asfixian a los nuestros. ¿De verdad creemos que flexibilizar hasta el 2027 salvará nuestras fábricas? No basta. No podemos resignarnos a ser el mercado de todos y el motor de nadie.\nNecesitamos acción, no excusas: incentivos reales a la producción local, apoyo decidido a la innovación y una política industrial firme que defienda nuestro mercado; porque proteger nuestra industria es proteger a nuestros trabajadores, a nuestras familias y nuestro futuro.\nNo esperemos a reaccionar cuando sea demasiado tarde. Actuemos ahora."
      }
    ],
