      },
      {
        "@value": "Yes, a lot has been achieved. Gas imports have decreased by two thirds, being replaced mostly by renewables and efficiency, which is a much more viable solution than replacing an old dependency with a new one, especially considering the slippery slope US democracy has gotten on.\nOil and coal are sanctioned, thus reaching the EU now via the ominous shadow fleet or via third countries. So what I want to see in the Commission's roadmap – besides, of course, doubling down on renewables and efficiency – is a clear concept to trace imports back to their source. We have to end the whitewashing of bloodstained Russian energy commodities."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
