      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_184"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "Those working for peaceful transition are asking us, the EU, for support, not to steer the wheel, but to be the wind in their backs; to support decisively, but not naively â decisively, because hesitation means losing this window of opportunity. We must ease sectoral sanctions that are crushing ordinary citizens. We need to support reconstruction, back democratic reforms and transitional justice, and ensure that the Syrian diaspora can contribute.\nIf we don't, others will fill the void, dear colleagues. But we must not support naively, because support must come with conditions: no new dictatorship, no new violence, no carving up the country like warlords, no exclusion of women opposition voices.\nAnd to the foreign powers still meddling in Syria â Turkey, Israel, Iran, Russia â this is not your chessboard. Let Syrians finally reclaim their own future.\nNone of this is easy. None of this is quick. Fighting erupted again over the weekend, fuelled yet again by external interference and foreign fighters. This is exactly the vicious circle that Syrians want to break and that this new government must break. That's why we need to step up our support â so that Syrians can rebuild their homes, heal their wounds and turn their country into a country for everyone.\n(The President cut off the speaker)"
      },
      {
        "@value": "As forças desestabilizadoras, alimentadas por narrativas nacionalistas e separatistas, são impulsionadas por potências que pretendem afastar a Bósnia‑Herzegovina do seu caminho europeu.\nPerante esta realidade, a União Europeia não pode hesitar. Precisamos de diálogo e precisamos de reforçar a nossa presença política e económica e de apoiar as reformas estruturais, para garantir que o país convirja rapidamente com os requisitos da União Europeia e não recue no seu processo de adesão.\nA história da Bósnia está intrinsecamente ligada à segurança dos Balcãs, que, por sua vez, está ligada à segurança da nossa Europa. Não fechemos os olhos."
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#timestamp": [
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-11T22:00:23"
      },
      {
        "@type": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#dateTime",
        "@value": "2025-03-12T22:34:59"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_372",
