      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#name": [
      {
        "@value": "Aleksandar Nikolic"
      },
      {
        "@value": "Matthieu Valet,"
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/contribution_241",
    "@type": [
      "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#Contribution"
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#identifier": [
      {
        "@value": "contribution_241"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#madeBy": [
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_176"
      },
      {
        "@id": "https://w3id.org/deliberation/resource/participant_30"
      }
    ],
    "https://w3id.org/deliberation/ontology#text": [
      {
        "@value": "But one major thing still remains and that is returns. Too many people without the right to stay in Europe are still in Europe. I would say it's quite hard to actually find Member States across Europe that are effective in their work that a no actually means a no. So, as the EPP, we have been calling for this proposal and we welcome it because we cannot have a system where people that are denied asylum can simply move to another Member State to avoid being returned. There must be clear rules, firm obligation and real consequences for non-compliance.\nI think this proposal in general creates now the common framework that we need. It closes many of the loopholes and it puts forward also a legal framework for return hubs. These are key messages that ensure that the people that do not have the right to stay in Europe also must leave Europe.\nBut this is only a starting point. Negotiations must make this proposal as strong and effective as possible. Our system demands results and I think that those days of wishful thinking are over. Now we need a policy that is in contact with reality and from EPP we are ready to deliver and we are ready to get to work."
      },
      {
        "@value": "Katsotaanpa kuitenkin komission tiedonannon otsikkoa. Siinä puhutaan osaamisunionista. Tämä ei ole sattumaa. Tämä on selkeä valinta, jolla yritetään edistää alati jatkuvaa EU:n syventymistä ja lipumista liittovaltion suuntaan.\nHyvät kollegat, se ei ole EU, joka ratkaisee nämä kysymykset osaamisen, koulutuksen, elinikäisen oppimisen tai työpaikkojen suhteen, eikä sen tulekaan olla. Koulutus- ja työllisyyspolitiikkaan liittyvät kysymykset ovat jäsenvaltioiden vastuulla ja niin niiden tuleekin olla. Päätöksenteon on pysyttävä jatkossakin kansallisissa käsissä."
      }
    ],
